The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
              
	Shukla is unwell   
	Bengal captain Laxmi Ratan Shukla is down with chicken pox and has been advised three weeks rest. I am still pretty weak and will take another two weeks to get completely cured. After that, I will start training. As of now, I am not playing any club matches, Shukla said.            
	 Nuruddin struck twice as Tollygunge Agragami beat Kalighat MS 2-0 in a CFL Premier Division match at the Rabindra Sarobar Stadium on Monday. The win ensured Tollygunge a place in the qualifying rounds of the second division of the I-League. BNR defeated Mohammedan AC 2-0 in another match.                
	Football: AFC Cup  East Bengal vs Al Nejmeh, Lebanon, (Salt Lake Stadium, 8:30pm)                                                                                                                                                      
